cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on DASH, a library of distributed data structures and algorithms designed for running applications on modern HPC architectures. It also discusses DART, a run-time system with an abstracted tier above existing one-sided communication libraries. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the implementation of PGAS (partitioned global address space) model in the form of C++ templates in DASH. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the use of C++ templates in DASH to implement PGAS model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although the paper does not explicitly discuss machine learning, the use of self-adaptive behavior in DASH applications could potentially fall under this category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses high-level features of DASH that enable more complex automatic transformations and optimizations in the future, which could fall under the category of software engineering.
